# Accountant Duck API

A small application to track and register deposits and extractions.

# Login [POST /login]

Used to login in the app.

It takes a JSON object called user, containing a name and a password.

+ name (string, required) - The username.
+ password (string, required) - The password for the username.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "user": {
                        "name": "USERNAME",
                        "password": "PASSWORD"
                    }
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "name": "USERNAME",
                "password": "0be64ae89ddd24e225434de95d501711339baeee18f009ba9b4369af27d30d60"
            }

# Logout [GET /logout]

Used to logout in the app.

+ Response 204

# Me [GET /me]

Used to see the attributes for the logged user.

+ Response 200

    + Body

            {
                "name": "USERNAME",
                "password": "0be64ae89ddd24e225434de95d501711339baeee18f009ba9b4369af27d30d60"
            }

# Group Movements

Resource related to movements in the API.

## Movements Collection [/movements]

### List all Movements [GET]

This endpoint return an array with all the movements attributes sorted by date.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            [
                {
                    "created_at": 2015-09-01",
                    "description": "initial balance",
                    "price": "1400",
                    "type": "Deposit",
                    "user_id": "1",
                    "id": "1"
                },
                {
                    "created_at": 2015-09-01",
                    "description": "money extraction",
                    "price": "400",
                    "type": "Extraction",
                    "user_id": "1",
                    "id": "2
                }
            ]

### Create a new Movement [POST]

Create a new movement using this action. It takes a JSON object movement
containing a description, price, type and created_at.

+ description (string, required) - The description of the movement.
+ price (string, required) - The amount of the transaction.
+ type (string, required) - The type of the movement.
+ created_at (string, required) - The date of the transaction.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "movement": {
                            "description": "initial balance",
                            "price": "1400",
                            "type": "Deposit",
                            "created_at": 2015-09-01"
                        }
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "description": "initial balance",
                "price": "1400",
                "type": "Deposit",
                "created_at": 2015-09-01",
                "id": "1"
            }

## Movement [/movements/{movement_id}]

+ Parameters
  + movement_id (number, required) - ID of the Movement in the form of a integer.

### View a Movement Detail [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
